<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-04-24a.3.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100321" speakername="Lord Hylton" colon="" colnum="3"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60424w01.htm#60424w01_wqn4">
	<p pid="a.3.1/1">asked Her Majesty's Government:</p>
	<p pid="a.3.1/2" qnum="HL5091">Whether they will resist the draft proposal from the European Commission which would allow 0.9 per cent. contamination of organic foods and feeding-stuffs by genetically modified commodities.</p>
</ques>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-04-24a.3.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-04-24b.3.2" matchtype="changes"/>
<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-04-24a.3.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100030" speakername="Lord Bach" colon=":" colnum="3"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60424w01.htm#60424w01_spmin4">
	<p pid="a.3.2/1">The Government will be consulting stakeholders on the proposed threshold for adventitious GM presence before deciding what our position should be. We are also committed to exploring whether a threshold lower than 0.9 per cent. should apply for organic production.</p>
</reply>
